# Demo
# A self-contained showcase for the drop-in DialogueBox. No `if:` / `do:`
# hooks, so it runs with zero game code. Each NPC beat is its own Scene
# (story mode = one NPC line per scene), linked with `=>`.

NPC: Guide

Guide:
Welcome to Gaba — this whole conversation is running from a plain .dlg file.
playback: auto_advance
=> Choose

Scene: Choose
Guide:
Pick a path. Both feel exactly the same to your players.

Player:
Tell me about voices.
=> Voices

Player:
Just finish the demo.
=> Done

Scene: Voices
Guide:
Add a vo: line to any beat and the optional grunt + gool tools speak it. Skip them and it stays text — voices are per-line optional.

Player:
Got it.
=> Done

Scene: Done
Guide:
That's the whole loop: write the lines, drop in a DialogueBox, ship. Press the advance key to close.
